@20001  = ~Rogue~
@20002  = ~ROGUE: To accomplish <PRO_HISHER> goals, for good or ill, the typical Rogue is a skilled pilferer. Cunning, nimbleness, and stealth are <PRO_HISHER> hallmarks. Whether <PRO_HESHE> turns <PRO_HISHER> talent against innocent passersby and wealthy merchants or oppressors and monsters is a choice for the Rogue to make.

CLASS FEATURES:

- May not wear armor heavier than studded leather.
- May not equip shields larger than bucklers.
- May only use the following weapons: long sword, short sword, katana, scimitar, dagger, club, quarterstaff, crossbow, shortbow, dart, sling.
- May only become Proficient (one slot) in any weapon class.
- May only become Proficient (one slot) in any fighting style.
- May distribute 20 points per level (30 at level 1) in thieving abilities: Open Locks, Pick Pockets, Find Traps, Move Silently, Hide In Shadows, Detect Illusion, Set Traps.
- Starts with base scores of 10% in Open Locks, 5% in Find Traps, 15% in Pick Pockets, 10% in Move Silently, and 5% in Hide in Shadows.
- May backstab for increased damage:
  Level 1-8: x2
  Level 9-17: x3
  Level 18+: x4
- May learn 'Rogue Feats' which provide the rogue with special abilities or passive bonuses. Rogues begin with three Rogue Feats, and may choose another at every odd level, up to level 19.

ROGUE FEATS: 
- Stealth Bonus (HiS/MS)
- Thieving Bonus (PP/OL)
- Detection Bonus (FT/DI)
- Lore Bonus
- Set Dart Trap
- Basic Alchemy
- Grease Jar/Smoke Bomb
- Flaming Weapon (requires Basic Alchemy)
- Set Fire Trap (requires Dart Trap and Alchemy)
- Armor Class Bonus
- Saving Throw Bonus (requires AC Bonus)
- THAC0 Bonus
- Backstab Bonus (requires THAC0 Bonus)
- Fighting Dirty
- Blind Opponent
- Disrupt Magic
- Illusion Magic (requires 15 INT, level 10+)
- Shadow Magic (requires 15 INT, level 10+)
- Use Wands (requires 12 INT, level 8+)
- Use Scrolls (requires 15 INT, level 8+)
- Luck Bonus

CLASS RESTRICTIONS:
- Alignment restricted to any except lawful good.
- Hit Die: d6

Prime Requisite For Dual-Classing: Dexterity
~
@20003  = ~ASSASSIN: This is a killer trained in discreet and efficient murder, relying on anonymity and surprise to perform <PRO_HISHER> task.

Abilities:
- Begins with the following rogue feats at 1st level: Stealth Bonus, THAC0 Bonus, and Melee Trick: Blind Opponent.
- May learn the Backstab Bonus feat up to three times, reaching a possible maximum multiplier of x7.
- May learn two special Assassin-only feats: Poison Weapon (Toxin) and Poison Trap.
~
@20004  = ~HUNTER: This rogue is skilled in tracking and capturing quarry - both beasts, and humanoids. Hunters are specially trained at their task and make fearsome opponents. They have honed their trap-making abilities well beyond that of the average rogue.

Abilities:
- Begins with the following rogue feats at 1st level: Detection Bonus, Dart Trap, and Basic Alchemy
- May learn two special feats unique to Hunters: Poison Weapon (Paralytic) and Web Trap.
~
@20005  = ~hunter~
@20006  = ~Hunter~
@20007  = ~SWASHBUCKLER: This rogue is part acrobat, part swords<PRO_MANWOMAN>, and part wit: the epitome of charm and grace.

Abilities:
- Begins with the following rogue feats at 1st level: AC Bonus, THAC0 Bonus, and Melee Trick: Trip Opponent.
- May repeat learning the AC Bonus and THAC0 Bonus feats, up to four times each.
- May learn two special Swashbuckler-only feats: Swashbuckling and Escape Artist. Swashbuckling is a temporary ability that increases the Swashbuckler's armor class. Escape Artist allows the Swashbuckler a chance to escape whenever Held, Webbed, or otherwise helpless.
- May Specialize (two slots) in any melee weapon available to Thieves.
- May place 3 slots into Two-Weapon Style.

Disadvantages:
- Swashbucklers have no backstab multipliers by default; they may raise it to a maximum of x2 by choosing the Backstab Bonus feat.
- May not learn any trap-setting feats.
~
@20008  = ~SHADOWDANCER: Shadowdancers can harness the power of shadow magic to increase their stealth abilities. Enigmatic and dangerous, these uniquely skilled rogues are able to blend seamlessly into the shadows in ways that a normal thief cannot, striking without warningâ€”sometimes with supernatural speed.

Abilities:
- Begins with the following rogue feats at 1st level: Stealth Bonus, Smoke Bomb, Grease Jar, and Saving Throws Bonus.
- May learn the Shadow Magic feat up to 5 times. This magical ability can mimic one of the following spells: Sanctuary, Blindness, Shadow Door, Shadowstep, or Summon Shadow.

Disadvantages:
- Alignment restricted to any non-lawful.
- -1 to base backstab multiplier compared to an unkitted Thief

Prime Requisites For Dual-Classing: Strength, Dexterity, Charisma~
