@20224  = ~Artful Dodging: when the rogue is targeted by a spell that can be evaded (Fireball, Lightning Bolt, etc.), the effects may be completely avoided upon a successful save vs. Breath. A helpless rogue (e.g. held, stunned, or asleep) cannot evade such effects, however.~
