Psionic powers are physically demanding, costing the rogue a temporary reduction in max hit points (3, 5, 7, or 9); for most powers these hit points are restored at a rate of 1/round. Some powers may be maintained indefinitely at a cost of an ongoing reduction in max hit points. In those cases the hit points re not restored until after the power has been canceled (at the same rate of 1/round). Maintainable powers are interrupted if the rogue is reduced to 25% hit points. Most rogues can only learn psionic powers from a single discipline.

CLASS RESTRICTIONS:
- Alignment restricted to any except lawful good.
- Hit Die: d6

Prime Requisites For Dual-Classing: Dexterity
~
@20501  = ~psypher~
@20502  = ~Psypher~
@20503  = ~PSYPHER: the Psypher is someone who (mostly) turns away from larcenous pursuits, and focuses on education and meditation to fully harness the power of the mind and the body. Psyphers are generally very well-educated and very healthy, treating their body as a temple. Through study and discipline, they can learn to use psychic abilities from any psionic discipline.

Abilities:
- Begins with access to the first power in all four psionic disciplines: Mind Thrust, Immobilize, Static Discharge, and Adrenaline Rush. The Psion can proceed to learn up to 10 more abilities, from any psionic discipline.
- Gains one extra hit point on every even level, up to level 20.

Restrictions:
- May only distribute 12 skill points per level into thief skills.
- May not Pick Pockets or Set Traps.
- May not be Chaotic.~
@20511  = ~soulblade~
@20512  = ~Soulblade~
@20513  = ~SOULBLADE: this warrior uses meditation to harness psychic powers in order to enhance <PRO_HISHER> martial abilities. Often training with Psionicists or Psyphers, the Soulblade can use a select few psionic abilities, generally those which fortify <PRO_HISHER> body or mind against attacks.

Abilities:
- Begins with access to the Adrenaline Rush and Kinetic Ram abilities. May learn another psionic ability every at every third level of experience, up to 18th level. The abilities that a Soulblade may learn include:
 -- from the Telekinesis discipline: Immobilize, Inertial Barrier, and Psychic Knife
 -- from the Biokinesis discipline: Metabolic Boost, Bioregeneration and Carapace
 -- from the Telepathy discipline: Intellect Fortress (at level 9)
 -- from the Pyrokinesis discipline: Static Discharge, Energy Absorption

Restrictions:
- Limited to light armors and weapons.
- Limited to Mastery (+++) with melee weapons.
- Limited to Proficiency (+) with ranged weapons.
- May not be Chaotic.
~
@20580  = ~Ultrablast~
@20581  = ~Ultrablast: this is a massive, omnidirectional psionic blast which savagely attacks the minds of the psion's enemies. All such enemies within 20 feet must save vs. Wands with a -3 penalty or be stunned for three rounds. 

Using this ability increases the psion's fatigue and causes a 25-point temporary reduction in <PRO_HISHER> max hit points.~
@20582  = ~Tower of Iron Will~
@20583  = ~Tower of Iron Will: this ability is similar to Intellect Fortress, protecting against any mind-affecting magic or psionics. However, in this case the psions can extend that protection to all allies within 20 feet. 

This is a maintainable power; it increases the psion's fatigue, and while in use, it causes a 25-point temporary reduction in <PRO_HISHER> max hit points. These hit points slowly return after the ability is canceled.~
@20584  = ~Cancel Tower of Iron Will~
@20585  = ~Earthquake~
@20586  = ~Earthquake: this ability causes a strong tremor to affect the ground nearby. All creatures in the vicinity take damage over the course of three rounds, and must make a saving throw or fall down in the first round.

Using this ability increases the psion's fatigue and causes a 25-point temporary reduction in <PRO_HISHER> max hit points.~
@20587  = ~Stasis Field~
@20588  = ~Stasis Field: this ability freezes all beings in the vicinity, at a molecular level. For twelve seconds the psion alone may move and interact with the frozen world. The stasis field prevents the psion from physically damaging anything during this time, but <PRO_HESHE> may initiate psionic abilities or magical powers, the effects of which will take place once the stasis ends. Beware: beings with godlike characteristics or powers may be immune to the effects of a stasis field.

Using this ability increases the psion's fatigue and causes a 25-point temporary reduction in <PRO_HISHER> max hit points.~
@20589  = ~Solar Flash~
@20590  = ~Solar Flash: this ability creates an intense ray of pure light energy to beam out at everyone within a 20-ft. radius of the psion. All enemies within the area of effect take 3d6 points of damage and must save vs. Spell or be blinded for 1 turn. Undead that are hit by the sunray take 20d6 damage.

Using this ability increases the psion's fatigue and causes a 25-point temporary reduction in <PRO_HISHER> max hit points.~
@20591  = ~Storm of Energy~
@20592  = ~Storm of Energy: this ability fills the vicinity with a churning storm of fire and electricity. For three rounds, enemies in the storm take 1d8 fire damage and 1d8 electrical damage (save for half).

Using this ability increases the psion's fatigue and causes a 25-point temporary reduction in <PRO_HISHER> max hit points.~
@20593  = ~Monstrous Evolution~
@20594  = ~Monstrous Evolution: this ability causes the psion's body to rapidly grow into a hideously powerful, hulking form. The monstrous form has an AC of -5, a THAC0 of 2 and attacks twice per round with powerful fists. These attacks do 3d6 crushing damage plus 2d4 poison damage. In this form the psion is immune to entanglement, web and hold effects, and to all poisons.

Upon resuming <PRO_HISHER> natural form, the psion becomes fatigued and suffers a 25-point temporary reduction in <PRO_HISHER> max hit points.~
@20595  = ~monster creature~
@20596  = ~Attack~
@20597  = ~Shapeshift natural form~
@20598  = ~Fission~
@20599  = ~Fission: this ability creates a fully functioning, fully cognizant clone of the psion. The clone has effectively 60% of the psion's experience and vitality, and operates according to the psion's will (since they are in fact the same person). Maintaining the clone's corporeal integrity involves a supreme act of will; the clone disintegrates after 1 turn.

Using this ability increases the psion's fatigue and causes a 25-point temporary reduction in <PRO_HISHER> max hit points.~
@20600  = ~Choosing this ability will enable you to choose another psionic ability. In addition, if you have learned at least four abilities in any of the four psionic disciplines, you will be able to learn one of two HLA-level powers from that discipline. The eight HLA-level psionic abilities are:

- Telepathy: Ultrablast. Causes all nearby enemies to make a saving throw or be stunned.
- Telepathy: Tower of Iron Will. This acts like the Intellect Fortress power, but protects all nearby allies while it is maintained.
- Telekinesis: Earthquake. This acts like the priest spell of the same name.
- Telekinesis: Stasis Field. This act's like the wizard spell Time Stop, but the psion cannot physically attack while the stasis field is active.
- Pyrokinesis: Solar Flash. This acts like the priest spell Sunray, but will not automatically kill undead creatures.
- Pyrokinesis: Energy Storm. This acts like the priest spell Storm of Vengeance, but with no accid or poison damage.
- Biokinesis: Monstrous Evolution. This ability transforms the psion into a hulking beast, similar in appearance to a Shambling Mound.
- Biokinesis: Fission. This acts like the wizard spell Simulacrum.

Unlike lesser psionic powers, these abilities may be used once per day. In each case, using the ability increases the psion's fatigue and causes a temporary reduction of 25 max hit points. Note: you may only learn one of the two ultimate powers in each discipline.~
@20601  = ~Telepathy~
@20602  = ~Telepathy: this feat confers the 'Mind Thrust' ability, and allows for learning more psionic abilities within the Telepathy discipline.~
@20603  = ~Id Insinuation~
@20604  = ~Id Insinuation: this ability attacks the target's subconscious, causing the target to go mad with fear for 3 rounds unless they save vs. wands with a -2 penalty. At 6th level the save penalty increases to -3, and at 12th level it increases to -4. The cost is 4 hit points.~
@20605  = ~Cancel Id Insinuation~
@20606  = ~Ego Repair~
@20607  = ~Ego Repair: this ability removes the effects of fear, sleep, feeblemindedness, unconsciousness, and intoxication, as well as berserk and confused states of mind. The cost is 5 hit points.~
@20608  = ~Cancel Ego Repair~
@20609  = ~Mental Domination~
@20610  = ~Mental Domination: this ability allows a psion to take over the mind of a creature for 5 rounds, unless the target makes a saving throw vs. wands. At 6th level the save is rolled with a -1 penalty, and at 12th level the penalty increases to -2. The cost is 7 hit points.~
@20611  = ~Cancel Domination~
@20612  = ~Intellect Fortress~
@20613  = ~Intellect Fortress: the psion erects a powerful mental defense against mental attacks, be they magical or psionic in nature. This is a maintainable power. The cost is 9 hit points.~
@20614  = ~Cancel Intellect Fortress~
@20615  = ~Psychic Crush~
@20616  = ~Psychic Crush: this ability initiates a powerful mental attack, stunning a target creature for 3 rounds unless the target saves vs. wands with a -2 penalty. At 6th level the penalty to the saving throw increases to -3, and at 12th level it increases to -4. The cost is 9 hit points.~
@20617  = ~Cancel Psychic Crush~
@20621  = ~Telekinesis~
@20622  = ~Telekinesis: this feat confers the 'Immobilize' ability, and allows for learning more psionic abilities within the Telekinesis discipline.~
@20623  = ~Immobilize~
@20624  = ~Immobilize: the target of this power is held frozen for 2 rounds upon a failed saving throw vs. wands, and then Slowed for 1 round while struggling to regain control of <PRO_HISHER> body. Even if the save is made, the target is briefly Slowed while fighting off the telekinetic control. At levels 6 and 12, the target's saving throw is rolled with a -1 and -2 penalty, respectively. The cost is 4 hit points.~
@20625  = ~Cancel Immobilization~
@20626  = ~Kinetic Ram~
@20627  = ~Kinetic Ram: this ability blasts a target with powerful but unfocused telekinetic energy, causing 2d3 crushing damage and, upon a failed save vs. wands, knocking the target back 10 feet. At 6th level the damage is 2d4 and the save is rolled with a -1 penalty; at 12th level the damage is 2d6 and the save is rolled with a -2 penalty. The cost is 5 hit points.~
@20628  = ~Cancel Kinetic Ram~
@20629  = ~Inertial Barrier~
@20630  = ~Inertial Barrier: this ability creates a movable barrier inches from the psion's skin, which has several protective effects: it provides a +2 bonus to AC and 40% damage resistance against crushing and missile attacks; a +1 AC bonus and 20% damage resistance against slashing attacks; 25% resistance to fire, acid, and magic damage; and immunity to the Magic Missile spell. This is a maintainable power. The cost is 7 hit points.~
@20631  = ~Cancel Inertial Barrier~
@20632  = ~Psychic Knife~
@20633  = ~Psychic Knife: the psion can focus telekinetic energy into a razor-sharp blade emanating from <PRO_HISHER> hand. This force can be wielded like a sword, as if the rogue had Mastery (+++) in its use, doing 2d3 slashing damage and 2d3 magic damage. This is a maintianable power. The cost is 7 hit points.~
@20634  = ~Cancel Psychic Knife~
@20635  = ~Instinctive Freedom~
@20636  = ~Instinctive Freedom: this ability is unlike most othes. The psion's mastery of the telekinetic discipline enables <PRO_HIMHER> to break free of any bonds; and to initiate the power at an instinctive level, whenever <PRO_HESHE> is helpless. The cost of the ability at the time it is triggered is 9 hit points.~
@20637  = ~Cancel Free Action~
@20641  = ~Pyrokinesis~
@20642  = ~Pyrokinesis: this feat confers the 'Static Transfer' ability, and allows for learning more psionic abilities within the Telepathy discipline.~
@20643  = ~Static Discharge~
@20644  = ~Static Discharge: this ability is similar to the Shocking Grasp wizard spell. The psion collects static electricity in his hand, and then uses it to attack an enemy. The enemy takes 2d4+1 points of damage, and must save vs. wands or be stunned for 1 round. At 6th level the damage is 3d4+2 and the save is rolled with a -1 penalty; at 12th level the damage is 4d4+3 and the save penalty increases to -2. The cost is 4 hit points.~
@20645  = ~Cancel Static Discharge~
@20646  = ~Energy Transfer~
@20647  = ~Energy Transfer: the immediate expenditure of energy to initiate this ability is converted into a steady bloom of positive energy in the target, resulting in a slow healing. At 1st level the target recovers 5 hit points over the cours of 10 rounds. At 6th level the target recovers 10 hit points over the same period, and at 12th level the target recovers 15 hit points over that time. The cost is 5 hit points.~
@20648  = ~Cancel Energy Transfer~
@20649  = ~Psychic Combustion~
@20650  = ~Psychic Combustion: this ability allows the psion to spontaneously create a brief but powerful fire in any location. The flames to 3d4+3 fire damage to all enemies within 5 feet of the flames. At 6th level the damage increases to 4d4+4, and at 12th level the damage increases to 5d4+5. The cost is 7 hit points.~
@20651  = ~Cancel Psychic Combustion~
@20652  = ~Energy Dispersion~
@20653  = ~Energy Dispersion: while this ability is maintained, the psion instinctively absorbs and deflects harmful energies. <PRO_HISHER> resistance to energy-based damage (fire, cold, electricity, and magic damage) is set to 75%. The cost to maintain the barrier is 9 hit points.~
@20654  = ~Cancel Energy Dispersion~
@20655  = ~Generate Lightning~
@20656  = ~Generate Lightning: after taking a few moments to collect static energy from the surrounding area, the rogue can discharge it as violent lightning energy. The lightning strikes a chosen target and arcs to any other enemies within 10 feet (the psion has some measure of control over the energy and can protect <PRO_HISHER> companions). The discharge does 2d6 lightning damage, which is halved upon a successful save vs. wands. At 6th level the damage is 3d6 and the save is rolled with a -1 penalty. At 12th level the damage is 4d6 and the save is rolled with a -2 penalty. The cost is 9 hit points.~
@20657  = ~Cancel Generate Lightning~
@20661  = ~Biokinesis~
@20662  = ~Biokinesis: this feat confers the 'Adrenaline Rush' ability, and allows for learning more psionic abilities within the Biokinesis discipline.~
@20663  = ~Adrenaline Rush~
@20664  = ~Adrenaline Rush: this ability temporarily boosts the psion's strength by 1 point and constitution by 2 points, for 4 rounds. Afterward, the psion becomes fatigued (-4 to STR) for 2 rounds. At 6th level the bonuses are increased to +2/+3, and at 12th level they are increased to +3/+4. The cost is 4 hit points, and the ability may not be used again until the fatigue has worn off.~
@20665  = ~Cancel Adrenaline Rush~
@20666  = ~Metabolic Boost~
@20667  = ~Metabolic Boost: this ability supercharges the psion's biological processes for 3 rounds, doubling movement speed and adding an extra attack per round, like the Haste wizard spell. At 6th level the effect lasts for 4 rounds, and at 12th level it lasts for 5 rounds. Afterward, the psion becomes fatigued (-4 to STR) for 2 rounds. The cost is 5 hit points.~
@20668  = ~Cancel Metabolic Boost~
@20669  = ~Bioregeneration~
@20670  = ~Bioregeneration: this ability triggers powerful healing responses in the psion's immune system, resulting in the regeneration of 1 hit point per round. This is a maintainable power; the psion can all such healing to fully take its course; however, the psion must concentrate on the power, and may not engage in physical combat while the power is maintained. At 6th level the psion regenerates 3 hit points every 2 rounds, and at 12th level the psion regenerates 3 hit points per round. The cost to maintain the regeneration is 7 hit points.~
@20671  = ~Cancel Bioregeneration~
@20672  = ~Camouflage~
@20673  = ~Camouflage: this ability makes the psion's body blend into the nearby environment like a chameleon. The effect is similar to the Improved Invisibility spell, without actually involving invisibility: the rogue has a -4 bonus to AC, a +40% bonus to stealth, and cannot easily be targeted by spellcasters. This is a maintainable power. The cost is 9 hit points.~
@20674  = ~Cancel Camouflage~
@20675  = ~Carapace~
@20676  = ~Carapace: this ability causes the rogue's skin to harden into a fast-growing, and strong but brittle shell. This provides a -2 bonus to AC, and harmlessly absorbs 1 physical attack each round. This is a maintainable power. The cost is 9 hit points.~
@20677  = ~Cancel Carapace~
